title.narrative: By the end of 2020 the child protection system is strengthened through the adoption of a child protection policy and a legalframework, a legal child focused system and an improved child protection mechanism.

description.narrative: The National Child Protection Policy was not finalised due to COVID-19-related constraints. The UNICEF-supported programme on alternative measures to detention for children in conflict with the law was expanded. However, due to court closures during the state of health emergency the proportion of children in pretrial detention increased to pre-2019 levels. A mapping of the social service workforce for children is underway. ;Two additional one stop centres for child victims of sexual violence became operational. UNICEF supported the elections of civil society representatives on the Independent National Commission for Human Rights and initiated a partnership with the national anti-corruption body. | Status:Partially met | As-of Date:12/01/2021
